rlArpSpoofing.name: rlArpSpoofing
rlArpSpoofing.organization: Radlan - a MARVELL company. Marvell Semiconductor, Inc.
rlArpSpoofing.description: This private MIB module defines ARP spoofing private MIBs.

rlArpSpoofingMibVersion.name: rlArpSpoofingMibVersion
rlArpSpoofingMibVersion.description: MIB's version, the current version is 1.

rlArpSpoofingTable.name: rlArpSpoofingTable
rlArpSpoofingTable.description: A list of the ifIndexes, IP addresses and corresponding MAC addresses.

rlArpSpoofingEntry.name: rlArpSpoofingEntry
rlArpSpoofingEntry.description: An entry of this table specifis ifIndex,IP Address and MAC address.

rlArpSpoofingIfIndex.name: rlArpSpoofingIfIndex
rlArpSpoofingIfIndex.description: The physical interface for which this entry contains information.

rlArpSpoofingLocalIpAddr.name: rlArpSpoofingLocalIpAddr
rlArpSpoofingLocalIpAddr.description: Ip addres for which the device will send ARP reply (ARP spoofing).

rlArpSpoofingMacAddr.name: rlArpSpoofingMacAddr
rlArpSpoofingMacAddr.description: MAC addres with which the device will send ARP reply. If the field is ommited or its value 0.0.0.0 the device will send with the interface's MAC address.

rlArpSpoofingRemoteIpAddr.name: rlArpSpoofingRemoteIpAddr
rlArpSpoofingRemoteIpAddr.description: Ip addres for which the device will send periodically ARP requests if its value differs from 0.0.0.0.

rlArpSpoofingOutPhysIfIndex.name: rlArpSpoofingOutPhysIfIndex
rlArpSpoofingOutPhysIfIndex.description: The physical interface to which the device will send periodically ARP requests if its value differs from 0. If its value is 0 then ARP requests will send to all the VLAN's ports.

rlArpSpoofingStatus.name: rlArpSpoofingStatus
rlArpSpoofingStatus.description: It is used to insert, update or delete an entry
